name: dejagnu

variants.name: build_system
variants.description: Build systems supported by the package

description:
DejaGnu is a framework for testing other programs. Its purpose is to
provide a single front end for all tests.

dependencies.name: expect
dependencies.description:
Expect is a tool for automating interactive applications such as telnet,
ftp, passwd, fsck, rlogin, tip, etc.

dependencies.name: gmake
dependencies.description:
GNU Make is a tool which controls the generation of executables and
other non-source files of a program from the program's source files.

dependencies.name: gnuconfig
dependencies.description:
The GNU config.guess and config.sub scripts versioned by timestamp.
This package can be used as a build dependency for autotools packages
that ship a tarball with outdated config.guess and config.sub files.

dependent_to.name: procps
dependent_to.description:
Command line and full screen utilities for browsing procfs, a "pseudo"
file system dynamically generated by the kernel to provide information
about the status of entries in its process table.

dependent_to.name: gcc
dependent_to.description:
The GNU Compiler Collection includes front ends for C, C++, Objective-C,
Fortran, Ada, and Go, as well as libraries for these languages.

dependent_to.name: binutils
dependent_to.description: GNU binutils, which contain the linker, assembler, objdump and others
